<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Click on the <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">tests</code> folder in the explorer — do you see <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">test_pawpal.py</code> inside it?</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">If it's empty, just create the file:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Right-click the <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">tests</code> folder → <strong>New File</strong> → name it <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">test_pawpal.py</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Paste the test code from the earlier artifact into it</li>
</ol>
